  <text>
      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary76.jpg"/>
            <dateline><date when="1862-06-10">Tuesday 10th</date> </dateline>
            <p>Having <name type="weather">rained</name> all night, we had no drill— until afternoon we had <orgName type="military ">Regimental</orgName>
               drill. <persName key="Santo" type="lieutenant">Santo</persName> and <persName key="Bobst" type="private">Bobst</persName> returned from <placeName type="city" cert="high" key="Beaufort" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl005">Beaufort<precision match="@ref" precision="high"/></placeName>. They say that <persName key="Phillips" type="private">Phillips</persName> has not
               yet been found. They had heard a report of a man found floating without <objectName type="clothing">shoes</objectName>
               and <objectName type="clothing">stockings</objectName>, answering to his description and then again they heard that he
               had been taken on by the <orgName key="military">9th New Jersey</orgName> Pickets — but nothing definite. <persName key="Mitchell" type="captain">Capt. Mitchell</persName> &amp; <persName key="Simms" type="captain">Capt. Simms</persName> <orgName type="military">51st New York</orgName> were here to see me today.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
  </text>
